Class Madness

  • java.lang.Object
    • Madness

  • public class Madness
extends java.lang.Object
    Madness is where the stats, collisions, locations of the cars, and more, are handled.

      • acelf

        public static float[][] acelf
        The Acceleration stat first value being how fast the car can move from rest (not moving). Second and third value meaning how much speed it gains while the car is moving

      • swits

        public static int[][] swits
        The Top Speed stat Take the values as if each one was a gear from a gearbox. 1st to 2nd, 2nd to 3rd, dependent on power obtained

      • handb

        public static int[] handb
        Handbrake power Basically, the braking power. Any negative value, would make you shoot forward instead of backward

      • airs

        public static float[] airs
        Aerial rotation If the value is too much, your car will just rotate rapidly and you can't control it.

      • airc

        public static int[] airc
        Aerial control This controls how high or low you'll go if you do flips, or how far you'll go if you do rollspins. This also effects the statbar of Aerial Control, but if this value is noticeably low, then the airs value will be used to display how much Aerial Control a car has.

      • clrad

        public static int[] clrad
        Collision radius "Clrad is the radius around each point that gets collided.. So if you have a car with so much points, you need the clrad to be low or it will get damaged very fast as so many points will get effected...If a car has low points you need the clrad to be bigger so the damage reaches other points or else the car will be indestructible..."
